Wolf Drake;-;Say Goodbye To Tomorrow Have you ever had that feeling of "Wow, summer is nearly over?" or maybe "It's almost the end of the month already?" Prepare to have that feeling over and over again while playing the masterpiece of Civilization V. This is the kind of game that almost literally sucks you in and immerses you in it's gameplay. Few games have the ability to keep you so focused that you lose track of time completely. One beautiful aspect of Sid Meier's Civilization V is how the game presents win conditions. In many games today, you're only given one option to finish a job and that's usually the option of killing everything on the screen. That isn't the case with Civ V. While you can fight your way to the top, you can also get through the game using clever diplomacy. Maybe instead of diplomacy you'd rather develop your country's scientific endeavors to win the space race. You might be the kind of person who prefers art and culture, though, so you could also focus on that and become the most cultured civilization ever known. All of these options are completely valid for clearing the game. ...And you will be clearing the game quite often because the replay value is tremendous. I thankfully bought all of the DLC while it was on sale, but the DLC is some of the best I've seen. After going through the base game several times, the added content took all of the weaknesses of the original game and revamped them into wonderful strengths. Overall, Civilization V has incredible value and it's nearly guaranteed you'll be spending a few nights huddled near the glow of your monitor with a bowl of microwaved food.
