Burger;-;AUDIO: Superb AESTHETIC: Impressive MEMORABILITY: Strong WORTH: Full Price PROS: Civilopedia and tutorials have gotten a bit of an upgrade from Civ4 and are now more palatable to new users. The game is workshop friendly and the community is actively perpetuating content for it. Expansions actually have purpose and add dimension to the game. With all these new features, the games depth and strategy is no longer confined to country tierlists. Hex-style grid was a great addition and feels very natural. CONS: As a long-standing fan of the Civilization series, I can't say I like the movement away from the board game feel of older installments (Civ2 and Civ3, specifically.) The graphics and animations are a bit unnecessary to me for this reason, though they are excellently-done and very beautiful. OVERALL: My qualms with this game are entirely from the point of nostalgia. At the end of the day, I'm willing to say goodbye to my virtual "Risk" board game in favor of what Civ is blossoming into as a series: a highly-complex strategy game that is a blast to share with like-minded friends. SCORE: 10/10
