Forsaken Avocado;-;Please love yourself and get this and all the DLC next time it goes 75% off, which is relatively often. I'm not sure how veterans to these sorts of turn-based strat games find it, but to a total newcomer like me the mechanics are rich and complex. It takes a while to become familiar with how everything works (I'm 150+ hours in and I'm still discovering things) but that just makes it more enjoyable in my opinion. You get out of it whatever you put into it. If you're super serious and looking for a challenge, this has it. If you're interested because you've heard of the potential hilarity that can ensue, this certainly has it. The worldbuilder DSK that comes with the game is also very enjoyable, especially if you're a writer or an artist. It's a great source of inspiration.
Galucia;-;When I look for a strategy game I'm interested in three things. I want a deep and rich strategy platform. Something that makes you think and really makes you feel like you are in control. All decisions good or bad will way into the outcome of the game and only when you are at your best will you obtain victory. I want this deep strategy but I also don't want it at the price of over complicating things. Too much of a good thing as they say, it needs to have that deep strategy but not get overly complicated about it. Last and most obviously the game needs to be entertaining. By this I mean that even if the game takes a while to complete, as most strategy games do, I want to enjoy the entire experience and not feel as though I am grinding through the game or spend un-necessary amounts of time just waiting for things to happen or finish happening. Civilization V hits this on all points. With every expansion the way to victory has become deeper and more rewarding without getting unbalanced or to complicated. Everything is very intuitive without being too simple. You really feel as though you are in control of a Civ and building your way to global domination and victory. Civilization has always been one of the best strategy games out there and the latest instalment continues this tradition. 9.5/10
