WYS MDubs;-;It's fun...............................................................................................................................................................................
[HL] 2-Dimensional;-;Civilization V is a strategy game by Firaxis Studios that supports both multiplayer and singleplayer. Unlike other strategy games I know, (*Cough cough* Starcraft II *cough cough*) this game does not have as huge of a learning curve to it. I was introduced to it at a fairly young age as both my brother and father were avid fans of the series. You start off usually by doing a single player game. Before you dive into the actual gameplay you must set up your game. First you are given a choice of factions, of which there are many. My favorite for the classic Civ is Egypt, while in Gods and Kings it is the Huns, and in Brave New World it is Brazil. After you select your faction, you select your land type (Islands, Continents, Fractal etc.) and game length. Getting started can be tough, but the helpful "Advisors" will show you the way. There are many ways to win, so finding your play style will not be a problem either. As you player you contruct buildings to help with different conditions, and units to help defend against or conquer your enemies. Just like the real world, world wonders of all different varieties can be constructed for your empire as well, however only one of each may exist. There are many as well, ranging anywhere from the Great Wall of China to the Big Ben. The different victory types are diplomatic, cultural, domination, science, and time. I personally have only won twice with both victories being cultural as Egypt and Rome. In addition, there is endless replayability. With the many different world types and Civilizations to choose from, gameplay is endless. You will be investing hundreds if not thousands of hours on this game, I assure you. Multiplayer is something to brag about as well, I have never had a better time anywhere than playing with friends on Civilization V. There are two expansions to this game, Gods and Kings and Brave New World. Each of these expansions are worth every penny. In the end, this game is spectacular and one of my all time favorites. If you can afford it, pick it up immediatly or if you don't have the cash, wait for a sale and then do yourself the favor. This game and all of it's expansions combined earns a 95/100 from me. Fantastic, amazing, superb. Get it.
