Flappy;-;This game is just straight up brilliant. If you can imagine it, my first ever Civilization game was Civilization Revolution on the Xbox 360, which compared to this game, is terrible. On that game I raged so much from the amount of random loses (E.G my 72 attack tank army getting taken out by freaking 42 defense pikeman, me and my friend called it 'Civi Logic') and this happened so often often, I rage quited sometimes. And I never rage quit in my other Startegy games (Rise of Nations, Command and Counquer etc). But then one of my friends out of the kindness of his heart gifted me this game, and I must say this is one of the best stratergy games I have ever played. I still haven't finished a game yet, because I love making new games with new nations, but you don't have to finish the game to enjoy it. It's immersive, has great balance and makes you think up stratergy after stratergy to try and take down Gandhi as quickly as possible. You will also sink a lot of hours into one game, my longest is about 7 hours, and as i have said, I havent finished a game yet. On the downside, there are some annoying things. Like some workers who ask you what task to do, even though you've already assigned them to make a mine or farm, and keep resetting every turn. Countries bonuses (Like Japan's Bushido in which your troops fight at full strength even if they are damaged) seem to fade quickly and seem to make no impact later on in the game. I also wish there was a way to change the city names (There probably is, I just have been lazy and not looked around for it) and a few more unique units for each civilization. This is the game for you if you love stratergy games, it is a wonderful bundle of goodness that makes you feel like you are controlling a nation, it's awesome, and it's definately worth your time. 9/10
