RustedRail;-;now that I've played over 1000 hours of Civ5 I feel that I should probably write a review. I've played the CIV franchise since CIV2 and I think that CIV 5 is by far the best. The game becomes more and more complex (especially with the expansion packs) and there are still a number of scenerios that I have barely touched. The game can be played from a number of different angles including cultural or military depending on your preferences and the leader you choose. The mods provide additional enjoyment from the ones I've tried. With my system, I tend to run the video options in the mid-range and have never crashed the game. This is using a Dell laptop. I hope they continue to release expansion packs as I'd like to see additional leaders offered going forward.
