ReliantGuyZ;-;In short, Civilization V is a delightful game of world domination. Anyone who enjoys board games such as Risk will enjoy the strategy in the game. I found plenty of complexity in the game, allowing the freedom to do pretty much anything that I wanted to do. The many different kinds of victory, whether it be through a blast of your military might, the triumphant noble plight of science, or via the slow creep of your empire's cultural dominance, allow for various options in deciding how you want to win. I haven't played any multiplayer, so I'm not an authority on that, but the large range of Civs included in the game allow for nearly infinite replayability, especially with the complexity-infusing expansion packs. I can tell you one thing though, the games are LONG. I literally blew threw 6 hours playing this game at one time, and there is no end in sight for that save. But yeah, wonderful game. Well thought through, well implemented, and always interesting. Highly suggest!
