Kuiper;-;I bought this game a week ago, and in that week's time, I managed to clock more than 40 hours. Nearly every waking moment that I wasn't at work was spent playing this game. That's kind of scary, and I think I'm going to uninstall this and not touch it for a long time, but that's in part because I think I've sort of exhasted most of what the game has to offer me at this point. Although the hex tiles are a HUGE improvement over previous games, compared to Civ 4, it feels like less of a strategy game and more of a tactics game, and there are other games that do tactics better than Civ 5. In terms of performance, I've been playing on a Sandy Bridge i3 with integrated graphics, and the game has been pretty smooth when using tactical view (replaces all tiles/units with 2D icons), which is how I have been playing the game for the past 20 hours, but running the game in "normal mode" makes it run like molasses for me, even when playing smaller games with 6 civilizations.
