[29th]WarriorPoet;-;I went into playing Civ 5 with a grain of salt. Civ4 was my very first computer game, and I remember being real excited when its sequel was announced. When I looked at many of the reviews for this game, they were very negative, saying that it was dumbed down and bad. I got this game, and I started playing... If you expect it to be a super-hard strategy game, well, you're going to be disappointed. But I don't think its dumbed down; it feels just like Civ4. There are a couple new mechanics, though none of them really effect gameplay in a big way. However, it's still just as easy and entertaining as 4. The gameplay is simple, (which I found particularly nice, considering that learning new mechanics would mess with my Civ4 habits) and yet is very engaging. I started playing this, worried whether ot not it'd be worth it, at about 1820: I stopped playing it at 2000. I felt like I was playing Civ4 with more countries and some new features. All in all, Civ5, no matter what you here, is worth the money. It has scenarios that I haven't even delved into yet, (in my opinion they were one of the best part of 4 and Warlords) and plenty of mod support. The graphics, obviously, are much better, which gives you something a little prettier to look at as you build your country. So what are you waiting for? BUY IT!!! Actually, buy Civ4 first and THEN buy this.
