NUDE DAD SURFIN THE WEB;-;Civ V is not every Civ player's cup of tea because it drastically changed Civ from its original formula. That said, I prefer this formula. No more 'stacks of doom' gameplay, and the new hex grid is much more aesthetically pleasing. Animated civ screens add a lot to the experience and make it feel less like you're playing against board game pieces and more playing against people. Civlopedia is great for people who love reading about any stuff about the civs that I didn't know without opening up wikipedia. Game mechanics are properly introduced to new players.
