mr shoe;-;Deep and satisfying game, with interlocking systems and overlapping objectives making play extremely compulsive. Factions have enough subtle differences and individual personality that it's always rewarding to replay as someone else, and the way random maps build so many stories of which cities rise and fall through fortunate resources or the placement of agressive neighbours is a delight. Sometimes the excellent sandbox pieces fall just short of fitting into as great a game though. Computer opponents are never really smart enough to impress, and higher difficulties increase the challenge more through unfair feeling bonuses rather than superior AI. For all the intricate depth of the technology and culture paths and alternative victory conditions to aim for it's also a bit of a shame that unless forced otherwise by setting extra rules a jack-of-all trades military strategy alway seems most powerful.
