Glorgoose;-;I really don't know where to start with this. Being able to put into words how I feel about this game is actually a little bit difficult. But I can say that it is my absolute favorite game. Now, at the beginning, when this game was just released, Civilization IV surpassed it in several ways, seeing as this game was missing some huge features (like religon and the like). By the release of the Gods and Kings expansion, I had grown to love this game as much, if not more than Civ IV. But with the release of Brave New World, it surpassed civ IV, it surpassed many of my favorite games, taking it's rightful place as my favorite game. The game covers the creation of the world, from the discovery of agriculture and the first settlements, to present day. You are the ruler of one civilization, and you start with a settler (who builds your first city), and another unit (typically a warrior of sorts), and from there, you can run your people however you want. You can focus on creating the mightiest military and crushing your foes, you can focus on diplomacy and getting city-states to do your bidding, maybe you want to focus on culture and produce magnificent works of art. There is so much to do, and you can dabble in pretty much all of it. It's really something else. All of this is built around a turn based strategy game. Unlike many 4X games though, figuring out how to play Civilization 5 is fairly easy. The tutorials are useful and easy to read, but even if you don't bother reading them, the UI makes everything quite straight-forward. Describing the game probably makes it sound a little bit dry, and you know what? It may not be everyone's cup of tea, but playing is believing. The game really has an addicting quality of it. You might say "just one more turn and then I'll quit" and then three hours later, you're nuking the Iroquois to stop them from building the last spaceship part before you can win the UN election you've worked so hard to achieve as Venice. Each game is exciting and can be different from the last. It's great! Please, get yourself this game! In particular, the complete edition is fantastic, which includes all the DLC civs and the two amazing expansions. It really is a fantastic game!
