PredatorDrone18;-;Okay, so, I would call the people reading this review just another group of filthy ing ers, which you ing are, but Valve doesn't like that anymore. Now, let's get one thing straight, right gere, right now: Valve consists of nothing but cool guys. Gabe is our lord and savior, and his disciples follow his teachings by the ing book. However, they have decided to censor swearing in the reviews. So, I guess either I have to cool it a little, or you guys have to start figuring out what I mean by ""; so y'all as better get real good at seeing the difference between hearts. Let's get started. Imagine that you're a citizen of the United States of America, or the United Kingdom, or maybe even Russia, and you want to control your country as they kick  in World War II (ADDITIONAL FEATURE: If you're from Russia, you can also fabricate a false history in which Russia doesn't ing suck from it's creation until present day.). You get to control a country from start to finish, doing as you please. You can focus on science, religion, warfare, or anything else. You can take over other empires,  churches and burning women. You have a huge--er--ing--load-bag-of-s-and--festivities-and-giant- amount of control in this game, and can rule how you please. Although Civilization V sacrifices historical accuracy for the sake of a good gaming experience, it does include some nods to the real empires of history, such as civilization-exclusive units. You can change the settings for a game or choose pre-made scenarios if you want more historically accurate gameplay, and you can play through real events, such as the fall of Rome. In conclusion, although I'm not a fan of the strategy genre, this game's addictive gameplay, endless replayability, and vast array of features earn it a 9/10 in my book.
