nykid10;-;First things first, my experience with Sid Meier games was virtually nonexistent about a year ago. I downloaded XCOM: Enemy Unkown for my ps3 and loved it! So, it made sense to try out Civilization V. It was highly recommended by some very close friends, and I was not disappointed. Civ V give you the opportunity to lead any of a number of nations throughout history, ranging from the ancient era to the information age. You are expected to create and maintain cities, build your armies, crush your enemies, spy on your opponents and ensure they do not steal your technology, engage in diplomatic relations with other countries and so much more. As the game progresses, your nation is given access to more advanced technology and your world becomes larger as you explore more of it. You can easily lose yourself for hours at a time in this game, and that is a great thing. This game is among the top in my personal gaming collection. It should be in yours too.
