runvus4;-;I first played Civ V back in 2010 on Windows. Then I switched over to Mac and couldn't bring myself to buy it again, especially as the original Mac version was just the Windows version in a WINE type emulator and sucked. After they released the OSX optimized version in March 2014, I couldn't resist getting it again. Much better performance now and not as laggy and graphics. On an iMac 27" at full resolution with high details is not choppy at all, but when scrolling fast it does pause to load the tiles one-by-one. Probably because the iMac I have only has 1gb of memory, not due any limitation of the OSX port. It does run the GPU hot hot hot and kicks the fans up to max still. Running it on a late 2012 Macbook Pro 13" retina got too hot to leave on the lap after half an hour and I could also get the tiles to load one-by-one due to the shared memory archetecture. An old octa-core 2009 Mac Pro with a Radeon 7970 had the PCI fans kick in a little higher but not in max airplane turbine mode. The tiles don't have to load one-by-one as much as the others, but it has 3gb of video memory. Gameplay is still the same addictive turn by turn, but the new-to-me Gods and Kings / Brave New World expansion packs and re-balancing forced a little adjustment my old tactics!
