Lewis;-;Welcome to Civilization 5; a turn-based strategy game where you are tasked with building the biggest empire and winning the game either by means of science, military, diplomacy or cultural influence. Choose the civilization you wish; whether that's sending Russia to space, or having Genghis Khan become world leader! What is good about this is that it is so immersive. You can really get stuck into a game and before you know it you're late for work. Yet while that is fairly undesirable, you can't help yourself from advancing into the next era, or hold off a few more turns until the Wonder you've been working on is completed, or even telling yourself you'll just keep playing till you win. Days may fly by, but the sense of achievement when you complete a game of Civ 5 is overwhelming, and makes you just feel pretty good! To play the game you will require a quick-thinking brain, as sometimes the slightest of decisions can result in finding an army on your front door, or could leave you at the bottom of the research table. To stay afloat, you must act fast and establish the means to produce a military quickly should you be attacked, but also to keep your research going. But don't have too many citizens, or your people will become unhappy! Great strategy game that will be played for years to come. Definately recommended!
