Megapower;-;It's a fun game I enjoy it when I have nothing to do. If you're interested in history, you'll probably like this. Even though it's fun, it has some technical problems. 1. The AI sucks, it does stupid moves and makes cities in 1-4 tiles islands with very limited resources. You can go to multiplayer to fix this, but multiplayer has its own share of problems 2. Multiplayer is buggy and needs work. Sometimes you loose connection and there is a noticable delay even with low ping. There's some other issues with it, but I'm going to try to keep this review short. 3. The game has long load times. It takes 2 minutes to load to the main menu screen on my laptop, 45-1 minute on my desktop. If you have a SSD, store this game on it. It'll help. UPDATE: Recently Aspyr ported this game to Linux. I have tried it and it suffers from some issues, some fixable and some ignorable. 4. If you're a Linux user, the game runs only in DirectX 9 mode. Other than that, the port is REALLY GOOD. Surprisingly, the game runs faster on Linux compared to Windows using the Intel Driver. On the requirements it says that the Intel HD 3xxx series wont work but I can confirm IT DOES with a workaround. There is artifacting text when the Steam Overlay is on, just turn it off or set the overlay settings to low, fixes the problem.
