Cuong;-;Sid Meier's Civilization V is one of the best additions to my Steam Library ever. At the moment I'm roughly a bit more than 200 hours into the game, which is personally a lot of time for me, and I still play several turns each week. Pros: + [Laptops] Does not require a mouse; playable on the go. I frequently travel by train and whenever it takes a while I grab my laptop and fire up Civ. + A large variety of civilizations to toy with, even more when you purchase DLC and expansion packs, with each their Unique Buildings, Units and Traits. + Four speed options for the patient and less patient ones (Me. I tried marathon mode, big mistake, but my OCD kicked in and I just had to finish it.) + A large amount of mechanics, the game is complex, but it's a great once you get the hang of everything. + For those who crave knowledge; the game gives accurate information about the civilizations, units and buildings. + Playable on tablets. Cons - Might feel repetitive for some - Noob-unfriendly IMO, I wouldn't try playing on "Normal" mode (Prince) or Online if you're not familiar to Civ or the strategy genre. - Time consuming, be prepared to lose a lot of time playing this game (and maybe some sleep once you get hooked) - Waging war with an AI on lower difficulty levels may be very boring and feel ridiculously easy. It's common knowledge among players that the AI is terrible naval warfare Conclusion Civlization V is not a game for those who crave intense action and immediate results. Civ V is for those who like to put their brain to work and play that chesslike "One step ahead" way, where a grave error can actually screw up your whole game. To the strategists out there I'd highly recommend the game and it's certainly worth its price. I avoid rating simply because a rating mostly doesn't do anything justice. A tip: Don't buy games or watch films just based on a rating and actually read reviews if you wish to consider something, you might bump into lots of cool things that are supposedly considered bad. Though if I were to actually rate Civ I'd say a 9.5/10 N.B.: I mentioned as one of the pros that Civilization is playable on tablets. Normally this is not possible if you have an Android tablet or iPad, but there is a way to stream your PC to a tablet using Splashtop, which is available for both Anrdoid and Apple products. There are several guides available online on how to do this.
