Danielhrz;-;An excellent turn based game. It's hard to describe the game in full- with the DLC and without, there's just so much to it. Without DLC, In game, there's diplomacy, warfare, alliances, and social policies that will shape the world of your civs and others. With the Gold edition (Gods and kings) there is improved diplomacy, religon, and espionage. Is your religon the only acceptable one? Are you curious about your enemies motives? With Brave New World, you can vote on pressing matters, and it completely reworks the culturally victory. From Arts funding to policies that limit armies and nuclear weapons; these things great enhance the game once the world congress is founded. For the cultural victory, you now have to spread your culture via tourism- once everyone loves your culture, you win. (Believe me, it's quite difficult) Over all, it's a great game. I really appreciate the work put into it, and I hope to spend countless more hours playing it.
