Chainsaws;-;A nice evolution of the classic Civ games if a bit simplified. Maybe expansion packs will fill in the gaps as they did with previous versions but I won't be finding out as it will take a lot of persuasion for me to buy another Civ game. My problem? Single player is reliable but multiplayer is atrocious, nearly two years after release it's just about possible to get a 4-player game going but gameplay is laggy regardless of connection speeds involved and as soon as a problem occurs it can take hours to get the game going again from saves if it's not a total loss. All Firaxis/2K seem interested in is churning out countless DLC as more keeps appearing even though the base game still isn't working properly. Such a shame. Edit: After a couple of years and as many expansions this game now has a lot more depth, the multiplayer issues are gone and my ire has subsided. I can wholeheartedly recommend this as a successor to the previous games and it's worth picking up the full edition when there's a sale on. Will I be buying the sequel/spinoff Beyond Earth then? Yes, but not until the full edition is in the sale because by then I can expect any bugs to have been resolved and the game to be filled out to its proper potential.
