Wolfy;-;Hello! Firaxis Games have really made an amazing game here. Yes, the base non-expanded game wasnt all that great, but it had the capacity to be awesome. Which, with the expansions, it did indeed become one of the greatest Turn Based Strategy games out there. Art is great, the tiles and units are stunningly good, and the overlay HUD fits just right with everything else. Mechanics are perfect, with the complete game (Expansions), and when you have a few friends handy. It makes for hours and hours of enjoyment, laughing at how radioactive Ghandi is, planning wars against that one all-powerful nemesis of yours, choosing religions and then proceeding to annoy the heck out of the other religious nations in the game by converting their cities. Its got everything needed for its genre folks, thats why its my most played game in my library. Price for the base game should drop 5 or so dollars maybe, the expansions as well, and the maps could be another dollar less. But the Complete Edition is almost a steal, that could go up to a 60 and still be good. A great recommendation, for both casual and competitive the game will keep you occupied for a long time. A warning though, you must buy the complete edition to really experience the greatness of the game, the base game feels incomplete without the expansions. ~Wolfy
