Canti;-;If you've played the previous game, you might be a little disappointed to find that various elements have been dumbed down or removed completely. There is no longer any corporation, religion or espionage, diplomacy has been simplified to the point of being almost broken and stealing enemy territory through superior culture output is gone altogether. Also, while only allowing 1 military unit per tile does eliminate the problem in previous games where you had massive stacks of troops that could mow down everything in their path, it does make it very hard to manage a large army during an invasion, and trying to conquer a city that has no land around it is a nightmare since units suffer huge penalties for attacking from water. The last major blow to this compared to the previous game is the number of bugs and crashes. It was severely unpolished at launch and it still isn't totally finished. There is currently still no Pitboss app, even though it has been promised since before launch.
