Valiantttt;-;I'd like to start of this review by stating that this was my first civilization game EVER and that I played most of the hours on the Gold edition version(Gods and kings). First off, I find it very good that the game has workshop support since there are neat little scenarios/civilizations/modes on the workshop and modding for PC gaming should always be encouraged+supported since I often see it ignored by major publishers. Graphics are fine for the type of game, it looks very pretty and the art style is good and clear to see what means what. Turnbased gameplay is nice and expected from a civilization game(from what I had heard), even though sometimes it feels very slow but this is mostly in the early game. This isn't a big problem however considering the turns go quickly since the AI doesn't have to make many calculations in that part. Speaking of the AI, sometimes it feels highly irrational and stupid because Diplomacy in CIV5(god and kings) is pretty useless because they will just invade you anyway even if they cannot beat your armies to seemingly just annoy you. However it does provide a good challenge even if it has to archieve that with cheats(I dislike this since AI should be able to beat you by being smart)so that is an issue if you like playing Singleplayer like I do, however multiplayer doesn't always work like it should because of network issues(with people I could normally play MP games with) The complexity of the game could have been better since it does feel like they dumbed it down a bit(I also play alot of grand strategy games from Paradox Interactive that are way more complex and this might have made my judgement a bit biased)considering what I've heard from previous iterations of the game. I do like the removal of doomstacks because that mechanic sounded very broken if I heard about it and CIV5 has a nice wonder system that makes you feel proud when you build one and annoyed when an enemy steals it from you. City states are nice and amusing because sometimes you can supply them with advanced weapons so you can fight a proxy war.
