Sir Pinkleton;-;I played a lot of Civilization 4 back in the day with my brother and went into this one kind of expecting the same thing, big mistake. - They've streamlined some of the annoying things like limiting your resources instead of having unlimited supplies. - They've improved the combat side by removing the stacking of units on a single tile and steam rolling over everything - They've also removed the need to build transports for continent naval invasion which for me is a major plus point. The downside however: - With the streamlining process is the lack of control over the finer details. - You can't select all your cities on the same content to mass produce units or buildings anymore. - You can't pull up a chart summarizing all the nations power or overall growth. Overall it is definitely a step in right direction but it lost a lot useful things along the way. 8/10
